findings.lower_chest: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdomen.hepatobiliary: The liver demonstrates homogeneous attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. Gallbladder is within normal limits.
abdomen.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation. No peripancreatic stranding.
abdomen.spleen: Normal size and attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions.

urinary.kidneys: Normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. No evidence of hydronephrosis. A round 2.2 x 1.9 cm hypodensity consistent with a renal cyst in the upper pole of the left kidney. No perinephric abnormality.

gastrointestinal.small_bowel: Normal caliber, wall thickness, and enhancement.
gastrointestinal.colon: Wall thickening of sigmoid and distal descending colon with significant adjacent fat stranding, enhancing diverticulae, and a small amount of adjacent free fluid.

abdomen.pelvis: Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis.
abdomen.reproductive_organs: Uterus is of normal size and enhancement. No evidence of adnexal abnormality bilaterally.
abdomen.lymph_nodes: No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy.
abdomen.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm. Mild atherosclerotic disease noted.
abdomen.bones: No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture. Sclerotic foci consistent with bone islands in the left acetabulum and right iliac crest.

laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
